
UCSC SuperPathway Database Toolkit


To get the dependencies

pip install pyaml
pip install networkx


To get the code:
git clone git://github.com/ucscCancer/pathway_tools.git


========================
Installation
========================

python setup.py build
python setup.py install

(Local install)
python setup.py install --user


========================
Developement
========================

Setup your PYTHONPATH
export PYTHONPATH=`pwd`/pathway_tools
Once you have the pathway toolkit:

========================
==The pathway_db tool
========================

----------

Get a copy of the database
./scripts/pathway_db.py sync

----------

Compile to a superpathway (paradigm format)
 ./scripts/pathway_db.py compile --paradigm > superpathway.pid 

----------

Check status of local Pathway Database
./scripts/pathway_db.py status

----------

Syncronize local copy of HUGO
./scripts/pathway_db.py hugo_sync

----------

Run checks on pathway record
./scripts/pathway_db.py check PID45669

----------

Commit changes done on pathway
./scripts/pathway_db.py commit PID45669


========================
==The network comparision tool
========================

Compare to the old super pathway
./scripts/network_compare.py <path/to/pid_110725_pathway.tab> pid_all_pathway.tab


========================
==The network converter tool 
========================


Convert Superpathway file, with GMT file into XGMML
./network_convert.py --in-paradigm pid_110725_pathway.tab --in-gmt output.gmt  --out-xgmml super.xgmml

----------

Convert XGMML file to paradigm network and gmt file
./network_convert.py --in-xgmml super.xgmml --out-gmt test.gmt --out-paradigm test.tab



Inference instructions (assumes Mac with 'ports' installed)


Download from 
https://github.com/kellrott/libdai (git clone git://github.com/kellrott/libdai.git)


sudo port install scons
sudo port install swig
sudo port install swig-python
sudo port install gmp


1. from libdai:
Build:
scons
(If impatient add '-j 4' to use 4 threads)

Install:
scons install --prefix=/opt/local
(you may have to sudo to install)

2. from libdai/swig:
LIBDAI_PATH=/opt/local python setup.py install

(or 'python setup.py install --user' if you want to do a local install)

Before use (so shared library can be found)
3. export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/local/lib

To test:
python

>>> import dai

Pathway toolkit

git clone git://github.com/ucscCancer/pathway_tools.git

export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/local/lib

python setup.py build
python setup.py test

Command line:

./scripts/pathway_infer.py -d tests/active_only.yaml -p tests/toy_pathway.tab -e active tests/toy_data.tab -s sample_1

Run EM:

./scripts/pathway_infer.py -d tests/active_only.yaml -p tests/toy_pathway.tab -e active tests/toy_data.tab -s sample_1 --em-mode


